The paper deals with resource allocation in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed mechanism uses reinforcement learning, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG) and specifically Q-learning, which is a type of reinforcement learning algorithm (cs.AI). The mechanism also involves decision-making based on the system state, which is a characteristic of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with optimizing the allocation of resources, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT).
